sentences: Jason Cole Critchlow (born February 25, 1998), known professionally as Jay Critch, is an American rapper, singer and songwriter.
He was born on February 25, 1998 to a Trinidadian mother and a British-Guyanese father.
Jay Critch's first major collaboration was with Rowdy Rebel on the song "Man Down" in 2015.
In 2016, he began uploading songs on SoundCloud.
He became the subject of widespread attention in 2016, when his song "Did It Again" was remixed by Rich the Kid, who signed him to Rich Forever Music in November.
In November 2018, as a newly signed artist, Jay Critch released his debut solo mixtape, Hood Favorite.
In December 2020, Jay Critch released his third mixtape, Signed with Love.
On May 5, 2021, Jay returned with his mixtape, Critch Tape.
He is currently signed with Rich Forever Music.
He became the subject of widespread attention in 2016, when his song "Did It Again" was remixed by Rich the Kid, who signed him to Rich Forever Music in November.
Their collaboration went viral, with the music video gaining over a million views in the first week of its release.
Announced just hours before its release, the project contains 23 songs, with features from Fivio Foreign, Lil Tjay, and Drakeo the Ruler, among others.
